The paper discusses a simultaneous generalization of the Karhunen-Loeve (PCA) and k-means algorithms for data exploration and compression, which are commonly studied in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), information theory (cs.IT), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also mentions image compression, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.IT, cs.NA, and cs.SI.
